<title>USA: Delft gets $50,000 US Commerce penalty.</title>
<headline>Delft gets $50,000 US Commerce penalty.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-06-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Commerce Department on Monday imposed a $50,000 civil penalty on Delft Instruments NV to settle allegations the firm made false statements over exports to Iraq and Jordan.</p>
<p>The department announced the settlement in a statement.</p>
<p>On five occasions between August 2, 1991, and February 10, 1992, Delft made false statements cnocerning whether members of its executive board knew that Delft had exported U.S.-origin thermal imaging prototypes to Iraq and Jordan without U.S. export licenses, Commerce alleged.</p>
<p>Delft pleaded guilty in 1992 to charges that it had violated the Arms export Control Act by exporting U.S.-origin thermal imaging prototypes to Iraq without the required license.</p>
<p>((-- Washington Newsroom (202) 898-8300))</p>
